title: Doesn’t sync, stuck at “[Snapshots] Waiting for torrents metadata: 0/87”
body:
#### System information

Erigon version: v2021.10.03-1073-g0e457ba9d 

OS & Version: Windows 10

Commit hash : 0e457ba9d7ef6e1e27d8229f335c55362a864dde

#### Expected behaviour
Sync Ethereum mainnet

#### Actual behaviour
I am trying to sync Ethereum mainnet from scratch, but even after running Erigon for 10+ hours the node doesn’t get past this status:
```
INFO[05-15|15:29:29.229] [Snapshots] Waiting for torrents metadata: 0/87
INFO[05-15|15:29:47.877] [p2p] GoodPeers                          eth66=51
```
I have tried with both the latest version from devel branch and alpha branch.
I am using Windows 10 and I’ve built erigon .exe using the .\wmake.ps1 method.

I am running erigon with these settings:
`erigon --syncmode=snap --datadir=D:\ETH_mainnet_erigon --port=30303`
I'm having the same issue with erigon for bsc on Windows 10, commit hash: 0e457ba9
likely your --torrent.port is not opened. check your firewall
I'm facing the same issue even after opening the port on my firewall
IMHO, opening ports for torrents shouldn't be an issue, I'm behind a shared internet environment in a co-living building, no way to open ports, and it works fine.
I can also run regular torrents just fine so I am confused why I can't run this correctly?

> likely your --torrent.port is not opened. check your firewall

I’m not admin of the router that handles my internet connection, so I cannot open ports. Other node clients like Geth work fine despite this, and torrenting with uTorrent etc.

> likely your --torrent.port is not opened. check your firewall

I even enabled DMZ to test it, it's not the ports
Same issue, I've went through manually opening the ports with new rules for the torrent port and nothing is working on windows

Try —torrent.port=0
